5000|$|In [...] "servicing" [...] practice, one {{check is}} made payable to the <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> {{instead of one}} to the <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> and one to the payee. The <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> {{receives}} the entire structured settlement payment, when due from the annuity issuer, takes what is owed to it and [...] "passes through" [...] the balance to the payee. This involves issuing a separate check to the payee issued off the <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> account.|$|E
