50|$|The {{discount}} rate is the fee a <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> charges {{to provide the}} factoring service. Since a formal factoring transaction involves the outright purchase of the invoice, the {{discount rate}} is typical stated {{as a percentage of}} the face value of the invoices. For instance, a <b>factoring</b> <b>company</b> may charge 5% for an invoice due in 45 days. In contrast, companies that do accounts receivable financing may charge per week or per month. Thus, an invoice financing company that charges 1% per week would result in a discount rate of 6-7% for the same invoice.|$|E
