5000|$|Once {{the account}} is set up, the {{business}} is ready to start funding invoices. Invoices are still approved on an individual basis, but most invoices can be funded in a business day or two, {{as long as they}} meet the factor’s criteria. Receivables are funded in two parts. The first part is the [...] "advance" [...] and covers 80% to 85% of the invoice value. This is deposited directly to the business's bank account. The remaining 15% to 20% is rebated, less the factoring fees, as soon as the invoice is paid in full to the <b>factoring</b> <b>company.</b>|$|E
